<p style=3D"text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style=3D"text-align: justify;"><strong>Description:</strong></p>
<p style=3D"text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style=3D"text-align: justify;">Be a part of a session on ETH Zurich, one=
 of the leading international universities for technology, by two represent=
atives from the institute. This talk will cover the following key informati=
on for engineering students to apply
 to ETH Zurich for higher studies.</p>
<ul>
<li>Universities and courses available for bachelor, masters and doctorate =
programs
</li><li>Eligibility to study in Switzerland </li><li>Application process <=
/li><li>Scholarship opportunities&nbsp;&nbsp; <br>
<br>
&nbsp;<br>
<br>
After the session, there will be a Q&amp;A round and interaction to answer =
any further questions.<br>
<br>
&nbsp;<br>
<br>
<strong>About ETH Zurich:</strong><br>
<br>
<strong>&nbsp;</strong><br>
<br>
ETH Zurich, Federal Institute of Technology has ranked 8<sup>th</sup> by QS=
 Ranking 2016 and&nbsp; ranked 9<sup>th</sup> by Times Ranking 2015. It has=
:</li></ul>
<ul>
<li>43 Master courses in technology like Mechanical Engineering , Robotics =
Systems and control, Biomedical&nbsp;
</li><li>Strong links with research and practice</li><li>22 spin-offs, 82 n=
ew patents, 298 cooperation agreements</li><li>Encourages entrepreneurial a=
pproach<br>
<br>
Speaker&#8217;s Bio <br>
<br>
<strong>Raghav Khanna</strong><br>
<br>
<strong>Doctoral student</strong> /&nbsp;<a href=3D"http://https/www.ethz.c=
h/en.html">Autonomous Systems Lab, ETH Zurich</a><br>
<br>
Raghav Khanna did his Bachelors in Mechanical Engineering from IIT Kanpur a=
nd his Masters at ETH Zurich where he was awarded the ETH Medal for buildin=
g a novel thermal energy storage for solar power during his master thesis. =
He is currently a graduate student
 at the Autonomous Systems Lab<br>
<br>
&nbsp;<br>
<br>
<strong>Stefan Bertschi</strong><br>
<br>
<strong>Engineer</strong> /&nbsp;<a href=3D"http://https/www.ethz.ch/en.htm=
l">Autonomous Systems Lab, ETH Zurich</a><br>
<br>
Stefan Bertschi is working as an engineer at the Autonomous Systems Lab of =
ETH Zurich since 9 years, where he leads the robotics laboratory, supports =
the research teams and established a school&nbsp;outreach&nbsp;program.<br>
<br>
&nbsp;</li></ul>
